The second most likely category is cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), as the paper deals with social networks and their properties. The third likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper discusses different centrality metrics and their performance in identifying influential nodes. The fourth likely category is cs.MA (Multiagent Systems), as the paper deals with the behavior of nodes in a network.
